1 Section 4041. Oklahoma Route 66 Commission Revolving Fund.
2 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
3 fund to be designated as the "Oklahoma Route 66 Commission Revolving
4 Fund", which shall consist of all monies appropriated, transferred,
5 or otherwise designated to the fund by law. The revolving fund
6 shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations,
7 and shall be under the administration of the Oklahoma Route 66
8 Commission. All monies accruing to the credit of said fund are
9 hereby appropriated, and shall be budgeted and expended in
10 accordance with the provisions of subsection B of this section for
11 the purpose of preserving and developing Route 66 and commemorating
12 the Route 66 Centennial.
13 B. No funds Funds shall be budgeted or expended from the
14 Oklahoma Route 66 Commission Revolving Fund prior to July 1, 2023,
15 or prior to the approval by the Legislature of promulgated permanent
16 in accordance with rules adopted by the Commission pursuant to the
17 provisions of the Administrative Procedures Act.
18 C. The Oklahoma Route 66 Commission shall promulgate, pursuant
19 to the provisions of the Administrative Procedures Act, permanent
20 rules subject to approval by the Legislature, to implement:
21 1. Application procedures for projects submitting requests for
22 funds;
23 2. Processes for awarding of funding applications;
24 3. Details of the Commission's general duties;
